	   <tr><td colspan=2>Actually, this is half true and half false.&nbsp;&nbsp;There is an item that helps heal you.  Its the Elder Spiritist Leggings from VS.  They right click Skin Like DIAMOND.  Now casting this buff on someoneone does heal them for the amount of HP the buff adds, so if you cast it over and over, each time it will add another 200hp aprox.  However, the downside to this is you wont be able to cast SLD on yourself if you have another one of your better HP buffs up which you probly would, like POG/PoTC/SLN/NS.  So yes there is an item that heals you, but you wont be able to use any of your better HP buffs if thats what you were useing the VS legs for was the heal up from manastone.<br><br>Treehugin<br>60th Druid<br>Defiant of Vallon Zek<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
